# Component Patterns & Conventions

## Component Organization
- **Feature-based structure**: Components grouped by domain (dashboard, home, authentication, checkout)
- **Co-location**: Related components in subdirectories (e.g., `components/dashboard/layout/`)
- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui components in [src/components/ui/](mdc:src/components/ui/)

## Naming Conventions
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `DashboardLandingPage`, `SignupForm`)
- **Files**: kebab-case matching component name (e.g., `dashboard-landing-page.tsx`)
- **Props Interfaces**: Named `Props` when simple, descriptive names for complex interfaces

## Component Structure
```tsx
// Export pattern - named exports preferred
export function ComponentName({ prop1, prop2 }: Props) {
  // Component logic
  return (
    <div>
      {/* JSX */}
    </div>
  );
}

// Props interface when needed
interface Props {
  prop1: string;
  prop2?: number;
}
```

## Client vs Server Components
- **Server Components**: Default, no directive needed
- **Client Components**: Must have `'use client'` at top
- **Examples**:
  - Server: [src/components/dashboard/landing/dashboard-landing-page.tsx](mdc:src/components/dashboard/landing/dashboard-landing-page.tsx)
  - Client: [src/components/home/home-page.tsx](mdc:src/components/home/home-page.tsx)

## Styling Patterns
- **Tailwind Classes**: Use `className` prop with Tailwind utilities
- **Conditional Classes**: Use `cn()` utility from [src/lib/utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts)
- **Custom CSS**: Import specific CSS files (e.g., `'../../styles/home-page.css'`)

## Component Composition
- **Layout Components**: Accept `children` prop with `ReactNode` type
- **Icon Usage**: Lucide React icons (configured in [components.json](mdc:components.json))
- **Image Handling**: Next.js `Image` component for optimized images

## State Management
- **Local State**: `useState` hook in client components
- **Form State**: Server actions for form submissions
- **Global State**: Supabase for user data and authentication

## Import Patterns
- **Relative Imports**: For same-level or nearby files
- **Absolute Imports**: Use `@/` alias for src directory
- **External Libraries**: Standard npm package imports
- **Example**: `import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';`